    • createIcuMap

      public static Map<TreatmentLevels,List<UkbEncounter>> createIcuMap(List<UkbEncounter> encounters, List<UkbEncounter> supplyContactEncounters, List<UkbLocation> locations, List<UkbProcedure> icuProcedures, InputCodeSettings inputCodeSettings, boolean useIcuUndiff)
      same procedure as createCurrentIcuMap, just for everything besides the current logic
      Parameters:
      encounters - A list with UkbEncounter resources.
      locations - A list with UkbLocation resources, to figure out which location is an icu location.
      icuProcedures - The UkbProcedure resources, which include information about ECMO / artificial ventilation periods.
      inputCodeSettings - The configuration of the parameterizable codes such as the observation codes or procedure codes.
      useIcuUndiff - If true, all ICU-related cases (ICU, ventilation, ECMO) are merged into the TreatmentLevels.ICU_UNDIFF category. If false, ICU cases are categorized separately into TreatmentLevels.ICU, TreatmentLevels.ICU_VENTILATION, and TreatmentLevels.ICU_ECMO.
      Returns:
      Map on which ICU cases are separated according to ICU, ventilation and Ecmo

    • generateSupplyContactToFacilityContactMap

      public static Map<String,String> generateSupplyContactToFacilityContactMap(List<UkbEncounter> supplyContactEncounters, List<UkbEncounter> departmentEncounters, List<UkbEncounter> facilityEncounters, boolean usePartOf)
      This method generates a mapping from supply contacts to facility contacts. The input sets are lists of UkbEncounter objects.
      Parameters:
      supplyContactEncounters - The list of supply contacts.
      departmentEncounters - The list of department contacts.
      facilityEncounters - The list of facility contacts.
      usePartOf - Use Encounter.getPartOf() attribute instead the visit number in Encounter.getIdentifier()
      Returns:
      A mapping from supply contacts to facility contacts.
      Throws:
      RuntimeException - if no encounter with an identifier.slice 'Aufnahmenummer' was found.

    • createCurrentIcuMap

      public static Map<TreatmentLevels,List<UkbEncounter>> createCurrentIcuMap(Map<TreatmentLevels,List<UkbEncounter>> mapIcuOverall, boolean useIcuUndiff)
      Create a map sorting the encounters according to their icu treatmentlevel, only for the current logic.

      If an icu patient got an active ventilation AND an ECMO, he will appear in all three lists. The sorting by hierarchy part will be done later in the data item generation

      Parameters:
      mapIcuOverall - The map generated in the createIcuMap(java.util.List<de.ukbonn.mwtek.utilities.fhir.resources.UkbEncounter>, java.util.List<de.ukbonn.mwtek.utilities.fhir.resources.UkbEncounter>, java.util.List<de.ukbonn.mwtek.utilities.fhir.resources.UkbLocation>, java.util.List<de.ukbonn.mwtek.utilities.fhir.resources.UkbProcedure>, de.ukbonn.mwtek.dashboardlogic.settings.InputCodeSettings, boolean) method.
      useIcuUndiff - Merge ICU+ items to TreatmentLevels.ICU_UNDIFF?
      Returns:
      Map Containing encounter which are currently in icu

    • createCumulativeMaxDebug

      public static void createCumulativeMaxDebug(List<UkbEncounter> listCumulativeEncounter, String treatmentLevel, Map<String,Map<String,List<String>>> resultMaxTreatmentCaseNrs)
      Fills the given map for debugging purposes, associating encounter case IDs with patients and treatment levels.
      Parameters:

      treatmentLevel - TreatmentLevel (e.g., TreatmentLevels.OUTPATIENT).
      resultMaxTreatmentCaseNrs - Map with the output, associating treatment levels with patients and their encounter case IDs. This map is modified and populated during the execution of the method.
